@dataclass
class Bots(scrapermost.endpoints.base.APIEndpoint): 
 12@dataclass
 13class Bots(APIEndpoint):
 14    """Class defining the Bots API endpoint.
 15
 16    Attributes
 17    ----------
 18    endpoint : str, default='bots'
 19        The endpoint path.
 20
 21    Methods
 22    -------
 23    create_bot(body_json)
 24        Create a new bot account on the system.
 25    get_bots(params)
 26        Get a page of a list of bots.
 27    patch_bot(bot_id, body_json)
 28        Update a bot partially by providing only the fields to update.
 29    get_bot(bot_id, include_deleted)
 30        Get a bot specified by its bot ID.
 31    disable_bot(bot_id)
 32        Disable a bot.
 33    enable_bot(bot_id)
 34        Enable a bot.
 35    assign_bot_to_user(bot_id, user_id)
 36        Assign a bot to a specified user.
 37    get_bot_lhs_icon(bot_id)
 38        Get a bot's Left-Hand Sidebar icon image.
 39    set_bot_lhs_icon(bot_id, image)
 40        Set a bot's Left-Hand Sidebar icon image.
 41    delete_bot_lhs_icon(bot_id)
 42        Delete a bot's Left-Hand Sidebar icon image.
 43
 44    """
 45
 46    endpoint: str = "bots"
 47
 48    @_ret_json
 49    def create_bot(
 50        self, body_json: Dict[str, Any]
 51    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
 52        """Create a new bot account on the system.
 53
 54        Parameters
 55        ----------
 56        body_json : dict
 57            The new bot settings as a dict.
 58            Example:
 59            {
 60                "username": "string",
 61                "display_name": "string",
 62                "description": "string"
 63            }
 64
 65        Returns
 66        -------
 67        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
 68        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
 69
 70        """
 71        return self.client.post(self.endpoint, body_json=body_json)
 72
 73    @_ret_json
 74    def get_bots(
 75        self, params: Dict[str, Any]
 76    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
 77        """Get a page of a list of bots.
 78
 79        Parameters
 80        ----------
 81        params : dict
 82            Query parameters to include.
 83            Example:
 84            {
 85                "page": 0,
 86                "per_page": 0,
 87                "include_deleted": true,
 88                "only_orphaned": false
 89            }
 90
 91        Returns
 92        -------
 93        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
 94        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
 95
 96        """
 97        return self.client.get(self.endpoint, params=params)
 98
 99    @_ret_json
100    def patch_bot(
101        self, bot_id: str, body_json: Dict[str, Any]
102    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
103        """Update a bot partially by providing only the fields to update.
104
105        Parameters
106        ----------
107        bot_id : str
108            Bot user ID.
109        body_json : dict
110            A JSON serializable object to include in the body of the request.
111
112        Returns
113        -------
114        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
115        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
116
117        """
118        return self.client.put(
119            f"{self.endpoint}/{bot_id}", body_json=body_json
120        )
121
122    @_ret_json
123    def get_bot(
124        self, bot_id: str, include_deleted: bool
125    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
126        """Get a bot specified by its bot ID.
127
128        Parameters
129        ----------
130        bot_id : str
131            Bot user ID.
132        include_deleted : bool
133            Whether deleted bots should be returned.
134
135        Returns
136        -------
137        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
138        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
139
140        """
141        return self.client.get(
142            f"{self.endpoint}/{bot_id}",
143            params={"include_deleted": include_deleted},
144        )
145
146    @_ret_json
147    def disable_bot(
148        self, bot_id: str
149    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
150        """Disable a bot.
151
152        Parameters
153        ----------
154        bot_id : str
155            Bot user ID.
156
157        Returns
158        -------
159        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
160        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
161
162        """
163        return self.client.post(f"{self.endpoint}/{bot_id}/disable")
164
165    @_ret_json
166    def enable_bot(
167        self, bot_id: str
168    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
169        """Enable a bot.
170
171        Parameters
172        ----------
173        bot_id : str
174            Bot user ID.
175
176        Returns
177        -------
178        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
179        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
180
181        """
182        return self.client.post(f"{self.endpoint}/{bot_id}/enable")
183
184    @_ret_json
185    def assign_bot_to_user(
186        self, bot_id: str, user_id: str
187    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
188        """Assign a bot to a specified user.
189
190        Parameters
191        ----------
192        bot_id : str
193            Bot user ID.
194        user_id : str
195            The user ID to assign the bot to.
196
197        Returns
198        -------
199        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
200        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
201
202        """
203        return self.client.post(f"{self.endpoint}/{bot_id}/assign/{user_id}")
204
205    @_ret_json
206    def get_bot_lhs_icon(
207        self, bot_id: str
208    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
209        """Get a bot's Left-Hand Sidebar icon image.
210
211        Parameters
212        ----------
213        bot_id : str
214            Bot user ID.
215
216        Returns
217        -------
218        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
219        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
220
221        """
222        return self.client.get(f"{self.endpoint}/{bot_id}/icon")
223
224    @_ret_json
225    def set_bot_lhs_icon(
226        self, bot_id: str, image: str
227    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
228        """Set a bot's Left-Hand Sidebar icon image.
229
230        Parameters
231        ----------
232        bot_id : str
233            Bot user ID.
234        image : str
235            The image's bytes string to be uploaded.
236
237        Returns
238        -------
239        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
240        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
241
242        """
243        return self.client.post(
244            f"{self.endpoint}/{bot_id}/icon",
245            files={"image": image},
246        )
247
248    @_ret_json
249    def delete_bot_lhs_icon(
250        self, bot_id: str
251    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
252        """Delete a bot's Left-Hand Sidebar icon image.
253
254        Parameters
255        ----------
256        bot_id : str
257            Bot user ID.
258
259        Returns
260        -------
261        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
262        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
263
264        """
265        return self.client.delete(f"{self.endpoint}/{bot_id}/icon")

Class defining the Bots API endpoint.

Attributes

endpoint : str, default='bots' The endpoint path.

Methods

create_bot(body_json) Create a new bot account on the system. get_bots(params) Get a page of a list of bots. patch_bot(bot_id, body_json) Update a bot partially by providing only the fields to update. get_bot(bot_id, include_deleted) Get a bot specified by its bot ID. disable_bot(bot_id) Disable a bot. enable_bot(bot_id) Enable a bot. assign_bot_to_user(bot_id, user_id) Assign a bot to a specified user. get_bot_lhs_icon(bot_id) Get a bot's Left-Hand Sidebar icon image. set_bot_lhs_icon(bot_id, image) Set a bot's Left-Hand Sidebar icon image. delete_bot_lhs_icon(bot_id) Delete a bot's Left-Hand Sidebar icon image.

class Channels(scrapermost.endpoints.base.APIEndpoint): 
 18@dataclass
 19class Channels(APIEndpoint):
 20    """Class defining the Channels API endpoint.
 21
 22    Attributes
 23    ----------
 24    endpoint : str, default='channels'
 25        The endpoint path.
 26
 27    Methods
 28    -------
 29    create_channel(body_json)
 30        Create a new channel.
 31    create_direct_message_channel(first_user_id, second_user_id)
 32        Create a new direct message channel between two users.
 33    create_group_message_channel(user_ids)
 34        Create a new group message channel to group of users.
 35    get_list_of_channels_by_ids(team_id, channel_ids)
 36        Get a list of public channels on a team by ID.
 37    get_channel(channel_id)
 38        Get channel from the provided channel ID string.
 39    update_channel(channel_id, body_json)
 40        Update a channel.
 41    delete_channel(channel_id)
 42        Archive a channel.
 43    patch_channel(channel_id, body_json)
 44        Update a channel partially by providing only the fields to update.
 45    restore_channel(channel_id)
 46        Restore channel from the provided channel ID string.
 47    get_channel_statistics(channel_id)
 48        Get statistics for a channel.
 49    get_channel_pinned_posts(channel_id)
 50        Get a list of pinned posts for channel.
 51    get_public_channels(team_id, page=0, per_page=60)
 52        Get a page of public channels on a team.
 53    get_deleted_channels(team_id, page=0, per_page=60)
 54        Get a page of deleted channels on a team.
 55    autocomplete_channels(team_id, name)
 56        Autocomplete public channels on a team.
 57    search_channels(team_id, term)
 58        Search public channels on a team.
 59    get_channel_by_name(team_id, channel_name)
 60        Get channel from the provided team ID and channel name strings.
 61    get_channel_by_name_and_team_name(team_name, channel_name)
 62        Get a channel from the provided team channel name strings.
 63    get_channel_members(channel_id, page=0, per_page=60)
 64        Get a page of members for a channel.
 65    add_user(channel_id, user_id, post_root_id=None)
 66        Add a user to a channel by creating a channel member object.
 67    get_channel_members_by_ids(channel_id, user_ids)
 68        Get a list of channel members based on the provided user IDs.
 69    get_channel_member(channel_id, user_id)
 70        Get a channel member.
 71    remove_channel_member(channel_id, user_id)
 72        Delete a channel member,removing them from the channel.
 73    update_channel_roles(channel_id, user_id, roles)
 74        Update a user's roles for a channel.
 75    update_scheme_derived_roles_of_channel_member(
 76            channel_id, user_id, body_json
 77        )
 78        Update the scheme-derived roles of a channel member.
 79    update_channel_notifications(channel_id, user_id, body_json)
 80        Update a user's notification properties for a channel.
 81    view_channel(user_id, channel_id, prev_channel_id=None)
 82        Perform all the actions involved in viewing a channel.
 83    get_channel_members_for_user(user_id, team_id)
 84        Get channel memberships and roles for a user.
 85    get_channels_for_user(user_id, team_id)
 86        Get all the channels on a team for a user.
 87    get_unread_messages(user_id, channel_id)
 88        Get the total unread messages and mentions for a channel for a user.
 89    set_channel_scheme(channel_id)
 90        Set a channel's scheme.
 91
 92    """

719    @_ret_json
720    def view_channel(
721        self, user_id: str, channel_id: str, prev_channel_id: str | None = None
722    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
723        """Perform all the actions involved in viewing a channel.
724
725        This includes marking channels as read, clearing push notifications,
726        and updating the active channel.
727
728        Parameters
729        ----------
730        user_id : str
731            User GUID.
732        channel_id : str
733            The channel ID that is being viewed. Use a blank string to indicate
734            that all channels have lost focus.
735        prev_channel_id : str, optional
736            The channel ID of the previous channel, used when switching
737            channels. Providing this ID will cause push notifications to
738            clear on the channel being switched to.
739
740        Returns
741        -------
742        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
743        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
744
745        """
746        options: Any = {"channel_id": channel_id}
747
748        if prev_channel_id:
749            options["prev_channel_id"] = prev_channel_id
750
751        return self.client.post(
752            f"{self.endpoint}/members/{user_id}/view", body_json=options
753        )

@dataclass
class Commands(scrapermost.endpoints.base.APIEndpoint): 
 13@dataclass
 14class Commands(APIEndpoint):
 15    """Class defining the Commands API endpoint.
 16
 17    Attributes
 18    ----------
 19    endpoint : str, default='commands'
 20        The endpoint path.
 21
 22    Methods
 23    -------
 24    create_command(body_json)
 25        Create a command for a team.
 26    list_commands_for_team(team_id, custom_only=False)
 27        List commands for a team.
 28    list_autocomplete_commands(team_id)
 29        List autocomplete commands in the team.
 30    update_command(command_id, body_json)
 31        Update a command.
 32    delete_command(command_id)
 33        Delete a command based on command ID string.
 34    generate_new_token(command_id)
 35        Generate a new token for the command based on command ID string.
 36    execute_command(channel_id, command)
 37        Execute a command on a team.
 38
 39    """
 40
 41    endpoint: str = "commands"
 42
 43    @_ret_json
 44    def create_command(
 45        self, body_json: Dict[str, Any]
 46    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
 47        """Create a command for a team.
 48
 49        Parameters
 50        ----------
 51        body_json : dict
 52            A JSON serializable object to include in the body of the request.
 53            Example:
 54            {
 55                "team_id": "string",
 56                "method": "string",
 57                "trigger": "string",
 58                "url": "string"
 59            }
 60
 61        Returns
 62        -------
 63        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
 64        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
 65
 66        """
 67        return self.client.post(self.endpoint, body_json=body_json)
 68
 69    @_ret_json
 70    def list_commands_for_team(
 71        self, team_id: str, custom_only: bool = False
 72    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
 73        """List commands for a team.
 74
 75        Parameters
 76        ----------
 77        team_id : str
 78            Team GUID.
 79        custom_only : bool, default=False
 80            Whether to get only the custom commands.
 81
 82        Returns
 83        -------
 84        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
 85        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
 86
 87        """
 88        return self.client.get(
 89            self.endpoint,
 90            params={"team_id": team_id, "custom_only": custom_only},
 91        )
 92
 93    @_ret_json
 94    def list_autocomplete_commands(
 95        self, team_id: str
 96    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
 97        """List autocomplete commands in the team.
 98
 99        Parameters
100        ----------
101        team_id : str
102            Team GUID.
103
104        Returns
105        -------
106        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
107        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
108
109        """
110        return self.client.get(
111            f"{Teams.endpoint}{team_id}/{self.endpoint}/autocomplete"
112        )
113
114    @_ret_json
115    def update_command(
116        self, command_id: str, body_json: Dict[str, Any]
117    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
118        """Update a command.
119
120        Parameters
121        ----------
122        command_id : str
123            ID of the command to update.
124        body_json : dict
125            The parameters to update as a dict.
126
127        Returns
128        -------
129        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
130        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
131
132        """
133        return self.client.put(
134            f"{self.endpoint}/{command_id}", body_json=body_json
135        )
136
137    @_ret_json
138    def delete_command(
139        self, command_id: str
140    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
141        """Delete a command based on command ID string.
142
143        Parameters
144        ----------
145        command_id : str
146            ID of the command to update.
147
148        Returns
149        -------

151        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response

153        """

155
156    @_ret_json
157    def generate_new_token(
158        self, command_id: str

172        """

176    def execute_command(

191        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
192        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
193
194        """
195        return self.client.post(
196            f"{self.endpoint}/execute",
197            body_json={"channel_id": channel_id, "command": command},
198        )

class Emoji(scrapermost.endpoints.base.APIEndpoint): 
 13@dataclass
 14class Emoji(APIEndpoint):
 15    """Class defining the Emoji API endpoint.
 16
 17    Attributes
 18    ----------
 19    endpoint : str, default='emoji'
 20        The endpoint path.
 21    get_emoji_list(page=0, per_page=60, sort='')
 22        Get a list of custom emoji.
 23    get_custom_emoji(emoji_id)
 24        Get some metadata for a custom emoji.
 25    delete_custom_emoji(emoji_id)
 26        Delete a custom emoji.
 27    get_custom_emoji_by_name(name)
 28        Get some metadata for a custom emoji using its name.
 29    get_custom_emoji_image(emoji_id)
 30        Get the image for a custom emoji.
 31    search_custom_emoji(term, prefix_only=None)
 32        Search for custom emoji by name based on search criteria.
 33    autocomplete_custom_emoji(name)
 34        Autocomplete custom emoji.
 35
 36    Methods
 37    -------
 38    create_custom_emoji(emoji_name, image)
 39        Create a custom emoji for the team.
 40
 41    """
 42
 43    endpoint: str = "emoji"
 44
 45    @_ret_json
 46    def create_custom_emoji(
 47        self, emoji_name: str, image: str
 48    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
 49        """Create a custom emoji for the team.
 50
 51        Parameters
 52        ----------
 53        emoji_name : str
 54            The emoji name.
 55        image : str
 56            The image's bytes string to be uploaded.
 57
 58        Returns
 59        -------
 60        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
 61        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
 62
 63        """
 64        emoji: Dict[str, Any] = {
 65            "name": emoji_name,
 66            "creator_id": self.client.user_id,
 67        }
 68
 69        return self.client.post(
 70            self.endpoint,
 71            data={"emoji": dumps(emoji)},
 72            files={"image": image},
 73        )
 74
 75    @_ret_json
 76    def get_emoji_list(
 77        self,
 78        page: int = 0,
 79        per_page: int = 60,
 80        sort: Literal["", "names"] = "",
 81    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:

 90        sort : '' or 'names', default=''
 91            Either blank for no sorting or "name" to sort by emoji names.
 92
 93        Returns
 94        -------
 95        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
 96        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
 97
 98        """
 99        return self.client.get(
100            self.endpoint,
101            params={"page": page, "per_page": per_page, "sort": sort},
102        )

 23    upload_file(channel_id, files)

 42        self, channel_id: str, files: Dict[str, Any]

 44        """Upload a file that can later be attached to a post.

 52

 56        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response

@dataclass
class OAuth(scrapermost.endpoints.base.APIEndpoint): 
 13@dataclass
 14class OAuth(APIEndpoint):
 15    """Class defining the OAuth API endpoint.
 16
 17    Attributes
 18    ----------
 19    endpoint : str, default='oauth'
 20        The endpoint path.
 21
 22    Methods
 23    -------
 24    register_oauth_app(body_json)
 25        Register an OAuth 2.0 client application.
 26    get_oauth_apps(page=0, per_page=60)
 27        Get a page of OAuth 2.0 client applications.
 28    get_oauth_app(app_id)
 29        Get an OAuth 2.0 client application.
 30    delete_oauth_app(app_id)
 31        Delete and unregister an OAuth 2.0 client application.
 32    regenerate_oauth_app_secret(app_id)
 33        Regenerate the client secret for an OAuth 2.0 client app.
 34    get_info_on_oauth_app(app_id)
 35        Get public information about an OAuth 2.0 client application.
 36    get_authorized_oauth_apps(user_id, page=0, per_page=60)
 37        Get a page of OAuth 2.0 client apps that can access user accounts.
 38
 39    """
 40
 41    endpoint: str = "oauth"
 42
 43    @_ret_json
 44    def register_oauth_app(
 45        self, body_json: Dict[str, Any]
 46    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
 47        """Register an OAuth 2.0 client application.
 48
 49        Parameters
 50        ----------
 51        body_json : dict
 52            The OAuth application settings as a dict.
 53            Example:
 54            {
 55                "name": "string",
 56                "description": "string",
 57                "icon_url": "string",
 58                "callback_urls": [
 59                    "string"
 60                ],
 61                "homepage": "string",
 62                "is_trusted": true
 63            }
 64
 65        Returns
 66        -------
 67        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
 68        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
 69
 70        """
 71        return self.client.post(f"{self.endpoint}/apps", body_json=body_json)
 72
 73    @_ret_json
 74    def get_oauth_apps(
 75        self, page: int = 0, per_page: int = 60
 76    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:

 15@dataclass
 16class Posts(APIEndpoint):
 17    """Class defining the Posts API endpoint.
 18
 19    Attributes
 20    ----------
 21    endpoint : str, default='posts'
 22        The endpoint path.
 23
 24    Methods
 25    -------
 26    create_post(body_json)
 27        Create a new post in a channel.
 28    create_ephemeral_post(body_json)
 29        Create a new ephemeral post in a channel.
 30    get_post(post_id)
 31        Get channel from the provided channel ID string.
 32    delete_post(post_id)
 33        Mark the post as deleted in the database.
 34    update_post(post_id, body_json)
 35        Update a post.
 36    patch_post(post_id, body_json)
 37        Update a post partially by providing only the fields to update.
 38    get_thread(post_id)
 39        Get a post and the rest of the posts in the same thread.
 40    get_list_of_flagged_posts(user_id)
 41        Get a page of flagged posts of a user provided user ID string.
 42    get_file_info_for_post(post_id)
 43        Get a list of information for the files attached to a post.
 44    get_posts_for_channel(channel_id, params)
 45        Get a page of posts in a channel.
 46    get_unread_posts_for_channel(user_id, channel_id, params=None)
 47        Get posts around oldest unread.
 48    search_for_team_posts(team_id, body_json)
 49        Search posts in the team and from the provided terms string.
 50    pin_post_to_channel(post_id)
 51        Pin a post to the channel.

 53        Unpin a post to the channel.
 54    perform_post_action(post_id, action_id)
 55        Perform a post action.
 56
 57    """
 58
 59    endpoint: str = "posts"
 60

 62    def create_post(
 63        self, body_json: Dict[str, Any]
 64    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
 65        """Create a new post in a channel.
 66
 67        To create the post as a comment on another post, provide root_id.

 71        body_json : dict

 73            Example:

 75                "channel_id": "string",

 79                    "string"
 80                ],
 81                "props": {}
 82            }
 83
 84        Returns
 85        -------
 86        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
 87        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
 88
 89        """

 52            }

 57        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response

 75        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
 76        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response

 51        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response

 53        """

@dataclass
class System(scrapermost.endpoints.base.APIEndpoint): 
 15@dataclass
 16class System(APIEndpoint):
 17    """Class defining the system API endpoint.
 18
 19    This endpoint has a mix of different endpoints, not only /system
 20
 21    Attributes
 22    ----------
 23    endpoint : str
 24        The endpoint path.
 25
 26    Methods
 27    -------
 28    check_system_health()
 29        Check system health.
 30    recycle_database_connection()
 31        Recycle database connections.
 32    send_test_email(body_json)
 33        Send a test email.
 34    get_configuration()
 35        Retrieve the current server configuration.
 36    update_configuration(body_json)
 37        Submit a new configuration for the server to use.
 38    reload_configuration()
 39        Reload the configuration file to pick up on any changes made to it.
 40    get_client_configuration(params)
 41        Get a subset of the server configuration needed by the client.
 42    upload_license_file(files)
 43        Upload a license to enable enterprise features.
 44    remove_license_file()
 45        Remove the license file from the server.
 46    get_client_license(params)
 47        Get a subset of the server license needed by the client.
 48    get_audits(page=0, per_page=60)
 49        Get a page of audits for all users on the system.
 50    invalidate_all_caches()
 51        Purge all the in-memory caches for the Mattermost server.
 52    get_logs(page=0, per_page=60)
 53        Get a page of server logs.
 54    add_log_message(level, message)
 55        Add log messages to the server logs.
 56    get_analytics(params)
 57        Get some analytics data about the system.
 58    get_configuration_environment()
 59        Get configuration made through environment variables.
 60    test_aws_s3_connection(body_json=None)
 61        Test AWS S3 connection.
 62
 63    """

Test AWS S3 connection.

Send a test to validate if can connect to AWS S3. Optionally provide a configuration in the request body to test. If no valid configuration is present in the request body the current server configuration will be tested.

body_json : dict, optional Mattermost configuration to test.

Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response

@dataclass
class Teams(scrapermost.endpoints.base.APIEndpoint): 
 13@dataclass
 14class Teams(APIEndpoint):
 15    """Class defining the Teams API endpoint.
 16
 17    Attributes
 18    ----------
 19    endpoint : str, default='teams'
 20        The endpoint path.
 21
 22    Methods
 23    -------
 24    create_team(name, diplay_name, channel_type)
 25        Create a new team on the system.
 26    get_teams(page=0, per_page=60, total_count=False, exclude_policy=False)
 27        Get teams.
 28    get_team(team_id)
 29        Get a team on the system.
 30    update_team(team_id, body_json)
 31        Update a team by providing the team object.
 32    delete_team(team_id, permanent=False)
 33        Mark the team as deleted in the database.
 34    patch_team(team_id, body_json)
 35        Update a team partially by providing only the fields to update.
 36    get_team_by_name(name)
 37        Get a team based on provided name string.
 38    search_teams(body_json)
 39        Search teams based on search term and options provided.
 40    check_team_exists(name)
 41        Check if the team exists based on a team name.
 42    get_user_teams(user_id)
 43        Get a list of teams that a user is on.
 44    get_team_members(team_id, page=0, per_page=60)
 45        Get a page team members list based on query string parameters.
 46    add_user_to_team(team_id, user_id)
 47        Add user to the team by user_id.
 48    add_user_to_team_from_invite(token)
 49        Add user to team from invite.
 50    add_multiple_users_to_team(team_id, users_per_team)
 51        Add a number of users to the team by user_id.
 52    get_team_members_for_user(user_id)
 53        Get a list of team members for a user.
 54    get_team_member(team_id, user_id)
 55        Get a team member on the system.
 56    remove_user_from_team(team_id, user_id)
 57        Remove user from team.
 58    get_team_members_by_id(team_id, user_ids)
 59        Get a list of team members based on a provided array of user IDs.
 60    get_team_stats(team_id)
 61        Get a team stats on the system.
 62    get_team_icon(team_id)
 63        Get the team icon of the team.
 64    set_team_icon(team_id, files)
 65        Set the team icon for the team.
 66    delete_team_icon(team_id)
 67        Remove the team icon for the team.
 68    update_team_member_roles(team_id, user_id, roles)
 69        Update a team member roles.
 70    update_scheme_derived_roles_of_team_member(team_id, user_id, body_json)
 71        Update a team member's scheme_admin/scheme_user properties.
 72    get_team_unreads_for_user(user_id)
 73        Get team unreads for a user.
 74    get_unreads_for_team(user_id, team_id)
 75        Get the unread mention and message counts for a team for a user.
 76    invite_users_to_team_by_mail(team_id, email_addresses)
 77        Invite users to the existing team using their email addresses.
 78    import_team_from_other_app(team_id, data)
 79        Import a team into a existing team.
 80    get_invite_info_for_team(invite_id)
 81        Get invite info for a team.
 82    set_team_scheme(team_id)
 83        Set a team's scheme.
 84
 85    """
 86
 87    endpoint: str = "teams"
 88
 89    @_ret_json
 90    def create_team(
 91        self, name: str, diplay_name: str, channel_type: Literal["O", "I"]
 92    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
 93        """Create a new team on the system.
 94
 95        Parameters
 96        ----------
 97        name : str
 98            Unique handler for a team, will be present in the team URL.
 99        diplay_name : str
100            Non-unique UI name for the team.
101        channel_type : 'O' or 'I
102            'O' for open, 'I' for invite only.
103
104        Returns
105        -------
106        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
107        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
108
109        """
110        options: Any = {
111            "name": name,
112            "display_name": diplay_name,
113            "type": channel_type,
114        }
115
116        return self.client.post(self.endpoint, body_json=options)
117
118    @_ret_json
119    def get_teams(
120        self,
121        page: int = 0,
122        per_page: int = 60,
123        total_count: bool = False,
124        exclude_policy: bool = False,
125    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
126        """Get teams.
127
128        Parameters
129        ----------
130        page : int, default=0
131            The page to select.
132        per_page : int, default=60
133            The number of members per page (max: 200).
134        total_count : bool, default=False
135            Appends a total count of returned teams inside the response object.
136        exclude_policy : bool, default=False
137            Whether to exclude teams which are part of a data retention policy.
138
139        Returns
140        -------
141        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
142        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
143
144        """
145        return self.client.get(
146            self.endpoint,
147            params={
148                "page": page,
149                "per_page": per_page,
150                "include_total_count": total_count,
151                "exclude_policy_constrained": exclude_policy,
152            },
153        )
154

@dataclass
class Users(scrapermost.endpoints.base.APIEndpoint): 
 12@dataclass
 13class Users(APIEndpoint):
 14    """Class defining the Users API endpoint.
 15
 16    Attributes
 17    ----------
 18    endpoint : str, default='users'
 19        The endpoint path.
 20
 21    Methods
 22    -------
 23    login_user(body_json)
 24        Login to Mattermost server.
 25    logout_user()
 26        Logout from the Mattermost server.
 27    create_user(body_json=None, params=None)
 28        Create a new user on the system.
 29    get_users(params=None)
 30        Get a page of a list of users.
 31    get_users_by_ids(body_json=None)
 32        Get a list of users based on a provided list of user IDs.
 33    get_users_by_usernames(body_json=None)
 34        Get a list of users based on a provided list of usernames.
 35    search_users(body_json=None)
 36        Get a list of users based on search criteria in the request body.
 37    autocomplete_users(params=None)
 38        Autocomplete users.
 39    get_stats()
 40        Get a total count of users in the system.
 41    get_user(user_id)
 42        Get a user a object.
 43    update_user(user_id, body_json=None)
 44        Update a user by providing the user object.
 45    deactivate_user(user_id)
 46        Deactivate the user.
 47    patch_user(user_id, body_json=None)
 48        Update a user partially.
 49    update_user_role(user_id, body_json=None)
 50        Update a user's system-level roles.
 51    update_user_active_status(user_id, body_json=None)
 52        Update user active or inactive status.
 53    get_user_profile_image(user_id)
 54        Get user's profile image.
 55    set_user_profile_image(user_id, files)
 56        Set user's profile image.
 57    get_user_by_username(username)
 58        Get a user object by providing a username.
 59    reset_password(body_json=None)
 60        Reset password.
 61    update_user_mfa(user_id, body_json=None)
 62        Activate multi-factor authentication for the user.
 63    generate_mfa(user_id)
 64        Generate an multi-factor authentication secret for a user.
 65    check_mfa(body_json=None)
 66        Check if a user has multi-factor authentication active.
 67    update_user_password(user_id, body_json=None)
 68        Update a user's password.
 69    send_password_reset_mail(body_json=None)
 70        Send an email containing a link for resetting the user's password.
 71    get_user_by_email(email)
 72        Get a user object by providing a user email.
 73    get_user_sessions(user_id)
 74        Get a list of sessions by providing the user GUID.
 75    revoke_user_session(user_id, body_json=None)
 76        Revoke a user session from the provided user ID and session ID.
 77    revoke_all_user_sessions(user_id)
 78        Revoke all user sessions from the provided user ID and session ID.
 79    attach_mobile_device(body_json=None)
 80        Attach a mobile device ID to the currently logged in session.
 81    get_user_audits(user_id)
 82        Get a list of audit by providing the user GUID.
 83    verify_user_email(body_json=None)
 84        Verify the email used by a user to sign-up their account with.
 85    send_verification_mail(body_json=None)
 86        Send verification email.
 87    create_user_access_token(user_id, body_json=None)
 88        Create a user access token.
 89    get_user_access_token(token_id)
 90        Get a user access token.
 91    disable_personal_access_token(body_json=None)
 92        Disable a personal access token.
 93    enable_personal_access_token(body_json=None)
 94        Re-enable a personal access token that has been disabled.
 95    search_tokens(body_json=None)
 96        Get a list of tokens based on search criteria in the request body.
 97    update_user_authentication_method(user_id, body_json=None)
 98        Update a user's authentication method.
 99
100    """
101
102    endpoint: str = "users"
103
104    def login_user(
105        self, body_json: Dict[str, Any] | None
106    ) -> Any | Awaitable[Any]:
107        """Login to Mattermost server.
108
109        Parameters
110        ----------
111        body_json : dict, optional
112            A JSON serializable object to include in the body of the request.
113
114        Returns
115        -------
116        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
117
118        """
119        return self.client.post(f"{self.endpoint}/login", body_json=body_json)
120
121    @_ret_json
122    def logout_user(self) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
123        """Logout from the Mattermost server.
124
125        Returns
126        -------
127        Any or Coroutine(...) -> Any
128        or requests.Response or Coroutine(...) -> requests.Response
129
130        """
131        return self.client.post(f"{self.endpoint}/logout")
132
133    @_ret_json
134    def create_user(
135        self,
136        body_json: Dict[str, Any] | None = None,
137        params: Dict[str, Any] | None = None,
138    ) -> Any | Response | Awaitable[Any | Response]:
139        """Create a new user on the system.
140
141        Password is required for email login. For other authentication types
142        such as LDAP or SAML, auth_data and auth_service fields are required.
143
144        Parameters
145        ----------
146        body_json : dict, optional
147            A JSON serializable object to include in the body of the request.
148        params : dict, optional
149            Query parameters to include.

Class defining the Users API endpoint.

Attributes

endpoint : str, default='users' The endpoint path.

Methods

login_user(body_json) Login to Mattermost server. logout_user() Logout from the Mattermost server. create_user(body_json=None, params=None) Create a new user on the system. get_users(params=None) Get a page of a list of users. get_users_by_ids(body_json=None) Get a list of users based on a provided list of user IDs. get_users_by_usernames(body_json=None) Get a list of users based on a provided list of usernames. search_users(body_json=None) Get a list of users based on search criteria in the request body. autocomplete_users(params=None) Autocomplete users. get_stats() Get a total count of users in the system. get_user(user_id) Get a user a object. update_user(user_id, body_json=None) Update a user by providing the user object. deactivate_user(user_id) Deactivate the user. patch_user(user_id, body_json=None) Update a user partially. update_user_role(user_id, body_json=None) Update a user's system-level roles. update_user_active_status(user_id, body_json=None) Update user active or inactive status. get_user_profile_image(user_id) Get user's profile image. set_user_profile_image(user_id, files) Set user's profile image. get_user_by_username(username) Get a user
